<doc id="1094574" wikidata="Q16909315" url="?curid=1094574" title="NCR 304">
<text>The NCR 304 computer, announced in 1957, first delivered in 1959, was National Cash Register (NCR)&#x27;s first transistor-based computer. The 304 was developed and manufactured in cooperation with General Electric, where it was also used internally. 

Its follow-on was the NCR 315.

