<doc id="1094689" wikidata="Q17070399" url="?curid=1094689" title="Luna, Rajasthan">
<text>Luna is a village in Rajasthan, India, famous as the birthplace of Mehdi Hassan. It is a panchayat village in Alsisar Tehsil of Jhunjhunu District.

Luna village might be the reference town for the famous motorette &#x27;Luna&#x27; which was manufactured by Kinetic Industries of Uttar Pradesh in the late 1980s.

==Demographics==
In the India census of 2001, the village of Luna had a population of 1,620. Males constituted 54.7% (886) of the population and females 45.3% (734), for a gender ratio of 828 females per thousand males.

==Notes==</text><links>
